      • writePageId

        private volatile long writePageId
        There's one free-list which both stable and unstable state (the state pages A/B) shares. Each free list page links to a potential next free-list page, by using the last entry containing page id to the next.

        Each entry in the the free list consist of a page id and the generation in which it was freed.

        Read pointer cannot go beyond entries belonging to stable generation. About the free-list id/offset variables below: 

         Every cell in picture contains generation, page id is omitted for briefness.
 StableGeneration   = 1
 UnstableGeneration = 2

        readPos                         writePos
        v                               v
  ┌───┬───┬───┬───┬───┬───┐   ┌───┬───┬───┬───┬───┬───┐
  │ 1 │ 1 │ 1 │ 2 │ 2 │ 2 │-->│ 2 │ 2 │   │   │   │   │
  └───┴───┴───┴───┴───┴───┘   └───┴───┴───┴───┴───┴───┘
  ^                           ^
  readPageId                  writePageId

      • acquireNewId

        public long acquireNewId​(long stableGeneration,
                         long unstableGeneration,
                         PageCursorTracer cursorTracer)
                  throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: IdProvider
        Acquires a page id, guaranteed to currently not be used. The bytes on the page at this id are all guaranteed to be zero at the point of returning from this method.
        Specified by:
        acquireNewId in interface IdProvider
        Parameters:
        stableGeneration - current stable generation.
        unstableGeneration - current unstable generation.
        cursorTracer - underlying page cache cursor access tracer
        Returns:
        page id guaranteed to current not be used and whose bytes are all zeros.

        IOException - on PageCursor error.
